Billionaire businessman, Obi Iyiegbu, popularly known as Obi Cubana, has met with the Lagos hawker who was seen in a video giving money to inmates in the Correctional Service van. Recall that the hawker identified as Ekuma Jeremiah was seen in a viral video giving money to inmates in a Nigerian Correctional Service van in Lagos. Following this act of kindness, Cubana, during an Instagram live interview hosted by Daddy Freeze, offered to sponsor the hawker’s tertiary education in any institution of his choice. Russia Says Expects Written US Response To Security Proposals… U.S., Russia Agree To Keep Talking After Meeting On Ukraine Obi Cubana has now met with Jeremiah in the company of Daddy Freeze, the man who shot the viral video, Rocky, and others in an effort to fulfill his promise. In a video shared on Daddy Freeze Facebook account, Cubana commended Jeremiah for his good gestures. The billionaire businessman also praised Rocky for bringing the hawker into the limelight.